main event: An unidentified bright shining white object was observed in Vineland, New Jersey on 26 May 1966.
interesting points: The object had a distinct conical to round shape,It was visible for a total duration of 11 minutes,Several witnesses reported seeing slow-moving objects alongside the bright object,The object made no sound and appeared to be very bright white,The object gradually faded out slowly in a horizontal direction.
witness description: A 16-year-old male who reported seeing the object and completed a questionnaire for the Air Force.
